## SSM Ubuntu EC2 Prod Summary Notes (Improved w/ Delegate Fix)

### 1. SSM Define & Uses
SSM: Manages EC2 via agent—no SSH/ports.
Uses: Patch/Session/Command/Inventory/State.

### 2. Patch Manager
Auto Ubuntu OS patching.
Prob: Vulns/downtime. Solve: Scheduled compliance.

### 3. Pre-reqs Ubuntu
1. sudo snap install amazon-ssm-agent --classic
2. sudo systemctl enable --now amazon-ssm-agent

### 4. Settings Actions (Exact)
**"Register delegated admin" → Enter Acct ID 5700-4374-7352 → CONFIRM**  
Why: Enables org Quick Setup/Explorer/Patch multi-acct.

**"Enable DHMC"**  
Why: Auto SSM role/agent ALL EC2.

**"Enable Auto Update"**  
Why: Agent auto-security 14d.

### 5. Baseline
Patch Manager > Create Custom > Ubuntu22.04 > Critical:7d auto > Create

### 6. Quick Setup Policy
Name:UbuntuPatch | Scan+Install Sun1AM | Tag:OS=Ubuntu ap-south-1 | 10%/5% | Create

### 7. Verify CLI
aws ssm send-command AWS-RunPatchBaseline Install Reboot=true --targets tag:OS=Ubuntu

### 8. Prod Practices
DHMC+Tags+Windows+Alerts. Dev test first.

### 9. Console Flow
1.Settings(DHMC) 2.Fleet(Online) 3.QuickSetup 4.Compliance

Delegate Acct ID fixes "No ID specified"—now prod-ready![web:2]
